JavaScript evaluates expressions from left to right.

+, -, *, **, /, %, ++, --, +=, -=, *=, /*, %=

Bitwise operators: are performed on 32 bits binary numbers. 
&, |, ~, ^, << (Zero fill left shift), >> (Signed right shift),
	>>> (Zero fill right shift)


